-- TAKE A LOOK-Britain's Tesco battling trading slump, accounting scandal 
-- By Sarah Young
-- Thu Oct 23, 2014 05:33AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Oct 17 (Reuters) - Tesco, Britain's biggest grocer and the world's third largest retailer, is reeling from an accounting scandal and a downturn in trading that has shaken investor confidence in the once mighty brand and wiped billions of pounds off its value.

